Working with Modules:

After tnering the context of a module after the "use" command followed by the module name we will need to set parameters.
We can use the "show options" command to list required parameters
All parameters are set using the same command syntax: set PARAMETER_NAME VALUE

Keep an eye on what command prompt we are in. Eg
- Regualr Command Prompt, no metasploit commands will work until we enter msfconsole
- msf, metasploit commands will work
- msf exploit(windows/smb/ms17_010_eternalblue), context specific commands only work
- meterpreter, meterpreter only commands here, an important payload connection
Once a meterpreter exploit is complete we can launch a shell on the target system which will allow us to run regular commands
